1. Switch Expressions (Standard) - JEP 361
What: Allows switch to return values.
Benefit: Makes code cleaner and eliminates the need for break statements.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Pattern Matching for instanceof (Preview) - JEP 305
What: Simplifies type checks and casting in one step.
Benefit: Reduces boilerplate code and enhances readability.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Helpful NullPointerExceptions - JEP 358
What: Provides more informative messages when a NullPointerException occurs.
Benefit: Helps developers quickly identify which variable was null, improving debugging.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. Records (Preview) - JEP 359
What: A new way to define immutable data classes.
Benefit: Reduces boilerplate code by automatically generating methods like equals(), hashCode(), and toString().
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. Text Blocks (Second Preview) - JEP 368
What: Multi-line string literals that preserve formatting.
Benefit: Makes it easier to work with long strings, such as SQL queries or JSON, without worrying about
escape sequences.